{
  "Line of Absolute Attack": {
    "rank": 1,
    "type": "Remolding",
    "approach": null,
    "skill": "Resolve",
    "flavor": """
      A remolding unit sweeps energy in a directed band, not a single point. Two adjacent spaces take the hit simultaneously. By the time the targets realize they were in the pattern, the damage is done.
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Activation:</h3>
      <p>As an Attack action, make a <strong>TN 2 Resolve check</strong> targeting two adjacent spaces 1–3 range bands away.</p>
      <h3>Effects:</h3>
      <p>If you succeed, deal elemental damage equal to your ranks in Resolve to all creatures and dolls in the target spaces.</p>
      <h3>New Opportunities:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>(op)+:</strong> Remove obscuring terrain from each selected space per (op) spent this way.</li>
        <li><strong>(op):</strong> Increase the number of adjacent spaces you can target by 1.</li>
        <li><strong>(op):</strong> Extend the range of this technique to 1–4 range bands.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
  "Sweeping Advance": {
    "rank": 2,
    "type": "Remolding",
    "approach": null,
    "skill": "Resolve",
    "flavor": """
      Obstacles stop being obstacles once you've run enough collapse energy through them. The sweep doesn't slow down for cover that isn't there anymore.
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Activation:</h3>
      <p>As an Attack action, make a <strong>TN 2 Resolve check</strong> targeting two adjacent spaces 1–3 range bands away.</p>
      <h3>Effects:</h3>
      <p>If you succeed, deal elemental damage equal to your ranks in Resolve to all creatures and dolls in the target spaces. You may remove dangerous, entangling, or obscuring terrain from each target space at no additional cost.</p>
      <h3>New Opportunities:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>(op):</strong> Increase the number of adjacent spaces you can target by 1.</li>
        <li><strong>(op):</strong> Extend the range of this technique to 1–4 range bands.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
  "Scorched Horizon": {
    "rank": 3,
    "type": "Remolding",
    "approach": null,
    "skill": "Resolve",
    "flavor": """
      Elevated positions offer a tactical advantage right up until the ground beneath them stops existing. Collapse energy doesn't respect high ground.
    """,
    "description": """
      <h3>Activation:</h3>
      <p>As an Attack action, make a <strong>TN 2 Resolve check</strong> targeting two adjacent spaces 1–3 range bands away.</p>
